@BestKindaWorst so the sort of trapped in glass style approval that comes with applause and an audience and fans or whatever feels so much safer a lot of the time. And it doesn't cause me to face my inner conflicted sense of self because they are cheering for the act! The persona!

@BestKindaWorst me. Uh but anyway the bad part is the more aloof or standoffish or honestly just not very kind a person is the more I end up craving that approval sometimes and that is what sucks, because I spend the whole friendship feeling bad and walking on eggshells and then it explodes...

@BestKindaWorst And idk I just love people, like really genuinely fully love people. I think it's hard to not get to know someone deeply and not love them even if I can't be friends with them or whatever. And I want to really be close to others. Idk people are the most exciting part of life for

@BestKindaWorst but because I've had so many harmful friendships, experienced a lot of rejection and also trauma/Trauma I need that sweet sweet reassurance I'm not a terrible bother or an annoyance or whatever. For the most part it's fine - though I do crave the vision of friendship from anime

@BestKindaWorst I tend not to get shy or intimidated or nervous until after the fact because I think my excitement for life and for other people kind of charges ahead so fast it takes the rest of me time to catch up. And I genuinely want to really know and feel close to people...

@BestKindaWorst I also love helping people laugh, smile, relax, feel pleasant surprise/whimsy/release so I love performing. I love the transformation of persona and so I also love being "on stage" in any form. I've always been comfortable with being the center of attention idk why...
